The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Feb. 7: Godrej Industries today said it will lease or sell its foods division. Shareholders have approved the proposal to sell its foods division through a postal ballot, Godrej informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. Shareholders have also approved an investment of up to Rs 10 crore in securities or in any other form of debt in Godrej Upstream Limited. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 7: The Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) today said it is in the process of preparing eight new accounting standards, including one each for insurance contracts and share-based payments like employee stock option schemes.

 New Delhi, Feb. 7: With a view to resolve the deadlock over the access deficit charge, Telecom Commission chairman and DoT secretary J.S. Sarma today met telecom regulator Pradip Baijal for the second time in the last five days.

 New Delhi, Feb. 7: Swedish telecom equipment firm Ericsson today committed to invest $100 million annually in India for the next few years, as it sees a potential in the Indian market.

 Mumbai, Feb. 7: Leading apparel group Pearl Global Ltd has decided to merge Pearl Styles Ltd and City Estates Pvt Ltd with itself.




